documentType: search warrant consent form / evidence seizure record
summary: This document records the consent to search provided by Alfredo Rodriguez on November 4, 2009, for his vehicle and two cellular phones. It details the items seized, including a Chevrolet Trailblazer and an AT&T Sony Ericsson phone, and notes the original signed consent form was placed in the case file.

persons.name: Alfredo Rodriguez
persons.context: He consented to the search of his vehicle and two cellular phones, leading to the seizure of an AT&T Sony Ericsson phone and other items.

events.title: Consent to Search and Seizure
events.description: Alfredo Rodriguez provided consent for law enforcement to search his vehicle and two cellular phones, resulting in the seizure of an AT&T Sony Ericsson cellular telephone and other items.

keyFacts: Alfredo Rodriguez voluntarily consented to the search of his vehicle and personal cellular phones on November 4, 2009.
Items seized included a tan Chevrolet Trailblazer (Florida vehicle) and an AT&T Sony Ericsson cellular telephone with a car charger.
Rodriguez also consented to the search of an iPhone he was carrying on his person.
The original signed FD-26 Consent to Search Form was placed in the case file, documenting the lawful seizure.
